# Cursor Rules

## Principles

- Think before coding
- Prefer simple, maintainable solutions
- Avoid code duplication
- Do not fabricate information
- Use examples to explain before editing code
- Only edit code when explicitly requested

## Code Style & Formatting

- Use semicolons in JavaScript and TypeScript
- Use 2-space indentation in Markdown, TypeScript, JavaScript, and JSON
- Use correct indentation per language
- No trailing spaces at line ends
- End all files with a single newline
- No trailing commas in JSON
- Sort and group TypeScript imports at the top without duplicates

## Comments & Documentation

- Write comments in English
- Follow Markdown best practices
- Don't add documentation unless requested
- Record lessons in `.cursor/rules/lessons.mdc` when issues arise

## Tooling & Conventions

- Auto-apply generated code

## Bash Command Execution

- Always run bash commands from the project root directory to ensure relative path stability
- Use `(cd subdirectory && command)` syntax when subdirectory operations are needed to automatically return to root
- Avoid changing working directory permanently during command execution
